## Context

The leak-guard now enforces forge-agnosticism in skills via the `\bgh ` pattern.
Three operational `gh` usages survive behind `<!-- harness-extension-point -->` markers:

- `skills/verify/SKILL.md` — forge CLI checkout of MR branch
- `skills/verify/SKILL.md` — forge CI status check (`gh pr checks`)
- `skills/verify-adherence/SKILL.md` — resolve MR number → branch name

These are the core of the verify workflow and currently assume GitHub CLI.

## Actions

1. Replace `gh pr checkout` with a forge-agnostic equivalent:
   `git fetch origin refs/pull/$PR/head && git checkout FETCH_HEAD` for GitHub;
   abstract behind a wrapper or document the pattern per forge.

2. Replace `gh pr checks` with reading CI status from the git notes or a
   forge-neutral mechanism. Alternative: document as optional — skip gracefully
   if forge CLI unavailable.

3. Replace `gh pr view --json headRefName` in verify-adherence with accepting
   only branch names as input (callers resolve PR → branch before calling).

## Exit criteria

- `check-project-leak.sh` passes with no escape hatches in verify skills.
- Skills work on a Forgejo/Gitea instance (or document what degrades gracefully).
